item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

[quote=“Mod Alexander, post:14, topic:319357”][quote author=badger41 link=topic=415820.msg3158588#msg3158588 date=1269286064]

2 problems, it went in fine, just the agile top and bottom are both placed as weapons, how do I move to correct spot?

1 problem, stop gravedigging.

PM the OP your message instead of bringing back a topic thats been dead…

Kid, are you dumb, what you just did was gravedigging, I asked a question, you damn moron.

your own argument with me just shows your stupidity. Good job.
[/quote]
If ur so smart answer the damn question![/quote]

go to your server sided code and click on item.java. For example say platebody ::pickup code is 8000 and legs are 8001. Put body number under
public static int body[] = {8000};
public static platebody[] = {8000};

put legs in
public static int legs[] = {8001};

Now Obviously there more numbers in between {} So put it like this
public static int legs[] = {7604, 8100};
Just separate the number with a comma and a space. Now promise me to never gravedig again. If you have more questions post a topic in Requests/help.
